\begin{slide}[toc=Processing]{Intelligence Consumption: Processing}
\textbf{Processing}: Movement of data or material towards a known goal or end result,
by passing it through a series of stages or a sequence of actions.\vspace{0.1in}
Convert our raw material, the selected intel defined by collection plan, and run it
through processing to normalize the information for inclusion into our knowledge management
function.
\begin{itemize}
 \item Read the narrative
 \item Document the relationships between significant data points
 \item Note important contextual clues (used in data theft? ransom? DDoS?)
 \item Attack models such as "Cyber Kill Chain" can be helpful for context
 \item Organize into consistent structured output, for storage. Always store
       original source document(s) and include references to them in output
\end{itemize}

Spreadsheets / CSV as output can be surprisingly effective

\end{slide}

\begin{slide}[toc=Knowledge Mgmt]{Intelligence Consumption: Knowledge Management}
Your program's intelligence in its \textit{final form}

\begin{itemize}
 \item Program's intelligence is published for broader audience
 \item Queryable
 \item Normalized $\rightarrow$ consistent $\rightarrow$ predictable
 \item Once organized, it becomes easier to reorganize
 \item Old raw collections are easy to search/retrieve. Periodically re-process
       old intelligence as program matures
\end{itemize}

The organization of this system is driven by two factors:
\begin{itemize}
 \item Minimize pivots and external investigation by event analysts (regular feedback to drive this)
 \item Support dynamic signature deployment, using queries on collected context, with minimal tool-local
       modifications chasing each new collection
\end{itemize}
\end{slide}

