\begin{slide}[toc=Analysis]{Intelligence Analysis}
Researching your collected intelligence to produce further intelligence that can
be leveraged by your program.\vspace{0.1in}

Examples:
\begin{itemize}
 \item Search for network indicators buried in lists of strings from EXEs
 \item Look across collected IP addresses associated with Corkow malware to
       identify network subnets containing 5 or more distinct IP addresses
       used for Command \& Control
 \item Gather domains associated with "APT28 campaign" (FireEye), to identify WHOIS
       information which is exclusively used for domains by that group
\end{itemize}

Preferred approach is to publish an internal analysis report, documenting conclusions
with supporting evidence, and meeting as many collection requirements as possible in
your narrative.\vspace{0.1in}

Feed the publication through your existing intelligence process:\\\textbf{Eat your own dog food}
\end{slide}

