\begin{slide}[toc=]{Intelligence Reporting}
Can be treated similarly to \textit{Analysis}, however also intended to inform an audience
outside of your security team. Summarize away deep technical details, but also consolidate
information from Analysis references into the same report.\vspace{0.1in}

Inside security team, treat just like analysis publications:
\begin{itemize}
 \item Simplifies program
 \item Helpful for training (your own team is in flux as much as the threat landscape)
 \item Queryable records for "Where and when have we reported this outside our team?"
\end{itemize}

\end{slide}

\begin{slide}[toc=Deployment]{Intelligence Deployment}
Deployment of intelligence describes delivering data from knowledge management into instructions
for your tools / systems to watch for it in your attack surface. Using metadata collected and
processed above, you can define static queries to retrieve intelligence stored in your program
appropriate for specific uses.\vspace{0.1in}

Example:
\begin{itemize}
 \item Process lists of IP addresses from known DDoS attacks
 \item Non-optimal to deploy them into Snort alerts
 \item Use Bro or similar to log connection-level metadata into elasticsearch
 \item Deploy to automated elasticsearch query that can report a single alert documenting
       all activity after exceeding a certain threshold
\end{itemize}

Return all IP address values into a JSON list where the IP address in CRITs contains at least one
metadata object of type "Historic Activity" who's value is "DDoS".

\end{slide}

